WHEN A HOLLYWOOD LEGEND VISITED ST MARGARETS
----------------------------------------------------------------------
    
    On Monday 8th July 1985 a production of Tennessee Williams's play
    "Sweet Bird of Youth", directed by Harold Pinter, opened at the
    Haymarket Theatre in London's West End. The star of the show was
    the sultry Hollywood star Lauren Bacall, the widow of Humphrey
    Bogart. It was an appropriate piece of casting. "Sweet Bird
    of Youth" written in 1959 tells of a fading movie star, Alexandria
    Del Lago, and her relationship with gigolo and drifter Chance
    Wayne. One commentator said that the part was written for Bacall,
    although Tennessee Williams had originally conceived it for
    Tallulah Bankhead.

